# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# pip-tools workflow
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file lists DIRECT dependencies only — unpinned or loosely pinned.
# Do NOT edit requirements.txt by hand; it is generated by pip-compile.
#
# To regenerate the pinned lockfile:
#   pip install pip-tools
#   pip-compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt
#
# To add a new dependency:
#   1. Add it here (requirements.in)
#   2. Run: pip-compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt
#   3. Commit both files together
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# IMPORTANT — coqui-tts install order
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# coqui-tts declares `encodec>=0.1.1` as a dependency.  encodec carries a
# non-OSI license that is restricted in certain corporate environments.
# To work around this, coqui-tts is installed with --no-deps and all its
# remaining deps are listed explicitly below.
#
# Install sequence (handled by install.sh):
#   1. pip install coqui-tts==0.27.1 --no-deps
#   2. pip install -r requirements.txt          (everything else)
#
# pip-compile can still resolve and pin all deps in step 2 correctly
# because coqui-tts itself is excluded from this file.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------

